{"meta": {"centerNodeId": "taxonomy-species-cyanoramphus-auriceps", "centerNodeType": "taxonomy", "generatedAt": "2026-05-28T16:28:22", "includedNodeCount": 3, "includedLinkCount": 2, "layoutMode": "precomputed-static"}, "center": {"id": "taxonomy-species-cyanoramphus-auriceps", "name": "Yellow-crowned parakeet", "type": "taxonomy"}, "nodes": [{"id": "taxonomy-genus-cyanoramphus", "name": "Cyanoramphus", "latinName": "Cyanoramphus", "type": "taxonomy", "taxonomyLevel": "genus", "summary": "Cyanoramphus（Cyanoramphus）是图谱中的分类级分类节点，当前关联7种鸟类，如反極綠鸚鵡、Red-crowned parakeet、新喀里多尼亞鸚鵡等7种鸟类。", "expandable": true, "memberCount": 7, "x": 465.35, "y": -172.17, "z": -65.9}, {"id": "taxonomy-species-cyanoramphus-auriceps", "name": "Yellow-crowned parakeet", "latinName": "Cyanoramphus auriceps", "type": "taxonomy", "taxonomyLevel": "species", "summary": "Yellow-crowned parakeet（Cyanoramphus auriceps）是图谱中的分类级分类节点，当前关联1种鸟类，如Yellow-crowned parakeet。", "expandable": true, "memberCount": 1, "x": -1524.27, "y": -1039.09, "z": 152.24}, {"id": "bird-yellow-crowned-parakeet-7b1bcfb4", "name": "Yellow-crowned parakeet", "englishName": "Yellow-crowned parakeet", "latinName": "Cyanoramphus auriceps", "type": "bird", "status": "NT", "summary": "The yellow-crowned parakeet (Cyanoramphus auriceps) also known as the yellow-fronted parakeet is a species of parakeet endemic to the islands of New Zealand. The species is found across the main three islands of New Zealand, North Island, South Island and Stewart Island/Rakiura, as well as on the subantarctic Auckland Islands. It has declined due to predation from introduced species such as stoats, although unlike the red-crowned parakeet, it has not been extirpated from the mainland of New Zealand. Its Māori name is kākāriki. History The yellow-crowned parakeet was once widely distributed across all of New Zealand, both the main islands and the outlying ones. However, due to both the aforementioned introduced mammals and human destruction of habitat, these parakeets have become much scarcer in the last few decades. While uncommon, they are still the most common parakeet in New Zealand. Taxonomy This species was first described by Heinrich Kuhl in 1820 and originally named Psittacus auriceps. Description Yellow-crowned parakeets are 23 cm long and primarily bright green. They have a red band fronting their eponymous golden crown. Their wings, when spread in flight, are bluish purple. Their eyes are either orange or red and their bill is grey. The males of this species are larger than the females. The females can also be distinguished from males as their bills are disproportionally smaller. Range and habitat Yellow-crowned parakeets prefer the upper canopies of tall, unbroken stub and forest, though they have been observed at high-altitude tussock meadows and on some of the subantarctic islands. A notably favoured habitat is mixed podocarp/nothofagus forest. The preference of C. auriceps for the upper canopies may have placed it at an advantage in comparison to the red-crowned parakeet, as it likely reduced the risk from predators. These parakeets are endemic to New Zealand and range across the main islands, as well as Ewing Island in the Auckland Islands. This is the world's most southern observed location of Cyanoramphus, and the second-southernmost location of living parrots. Diet Yellow-crowned parakeets subsist on the seeds of beech, flax, and tussock, but also eat fruits, flowers, leaves, shoots, and invertebrates. Reproduction These birds build nests in crevices, burrows, and trunks of trees depending on the habitat. Their eggs are white. Conservation The yellow-crowned parakeet is absolutely protected under New Zealand's Wildlife Act 1953. The species is also listed under Appendix II of the Convention on International Trade in Endangered Species of Wild Fauna and Flora (CITES) meaning international export/import (including parts and derivatives) is regulated. References", "shortSummary": "The yellow-crowned parakeet (Cyanoramphus auriceps) also known as the yellow-fronted parakeet is a species of parakeet endemic to the islan…", "locations": ["北島 (紐西蘭)", "南島 (新西蘭)", "斯圖爾特島", "奥克兰群岛"], "lat": -39.0, "lng": 176.0, "imageUrl": "https://upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/commons/thumb/9/9c/Kakaariki.jpg/960px-Kakaariki.jpg", "kingdomId": "taxonomy-kingdom-animalia", "phylumId": "taxonomy-phylum-chordata", "classId": "taxonomy-class-aves", "genusId": "taxonomy-genus-cyanoramphus", "speciesId": "taxonomy-species-cyanoramphus-auriceps", "taxonomyIds": {"kingdom": "taxonomy-kingdom-animalia", "phylum": "taxonomy-phylum-chordata", "class": "taxonomy-class-aves", "genus": "taxonomy-genus-cyanoramphus", "species": "taxonomy-species-cyanoramphus-auriceps"}, "expandable": true, "x": -1524.27, "y": -1039.09, "z": 137.65}], "links": [{"key": "bird-yellow-crowned-parakeet-7b1bcfb4__belongs_to_species__taxonomy-species-cyanoramphus-auriceps", "source": "bird-yellow-crowned-parakeet-7b1bcfb4", "target": "taxonomy-species-cyanoramphus-auriceps", "relation": "belongs_to_species", "label": "属于种", "evidence": "依据 birds.csv 中的种字段补充。"}, {"key": "taxonomy-species-cyanoramphus-auriceps__belongs_to_genus__taxonomy-genus-cyanoramphus", "source": "taxonomy-species-cyanoramphus-auriceps", "target": "taxonomy-genus-cyanoramphus", "relation": "belongs_to_genus", "label": "属于属", "evidence": "依据 birds.csv 分类字段补充：Yellow-crowned parakeet 属于属 Cyanoramphus。"}]}
